channel.title: Favor
channel.description:
I was wondering if someone could do me a favor... Tomorrow for school I have this project due, and I'll need to record my voice doing some speaking. The assignment is making a commercial about a Julius Caesar theme park. My voice, however, is not apt to do things such as this, and I was wondering if anyone with a good voice could record them self saying a short script (about 1:30 long).
You'll be in the credits :D

item.title: Favor
item.dc:creator: @reyx7 reyx7
item.description:
@reyx7 wrote:

Here is a script if anyone wants to take a crack at it:

Are you bored?
Do you have to read Julius Caesar for class?
Well then come on down to the Julius Caesar theme park!

We offer many attractions, including:

The Rides of March - take a tour to learn about the rise and fall of Julius Caesar on this amazing roller coaster. Experience the leader’s rise to power, his death at the peak of the roller coaster, and the exciting fall down!

Next is Ask a Soothsayer - Find out whether or not you’ll get stabbed by your friends later on

Pin the knife in the Caesar - Do you have what it takes to be a conspirator? Get 23 tries to put the knife in him!

Come try our famous buffet, serving dishes such as: Caesar salad, “baby ‘stabbed in the back’ ribs”, "Caesar ‘Nacho Leader’ chips, “Anton-on (an-ton-yun) rings”, a “Cassi-role”, “diet Casca”, and our famous Orange Julius.

How about our Ampitheatre? See daily presentations, including: Brutus explaining why he killed Caesar, and Antony’s reaction to Caesar’s death. After midnight, ghost stories with Caesar’s ghost.

The Colosseum, which was payed for by the insane amount of taxes levied by Julius Caesar. Watch lions eat the people who didn’t pay taxes!

So if you’re in need to get a vacation of history, head on down to the Julius Caesar theme park!
